doc.previous: On October 26, 2008, Alaska launched service from Seattle to Minneapolis-Saint Paul.[42] On August 3, 2009, service from Seattle to Austin, Texas began.[43] Service from Seattle to Houston began on September 23, 2009[44] and from Seattle to Atlanta on October 23, 2009.[45]
after: In March 2010, Alaska Airlines began service from San Jose, California to Kahului and Kona, Hawaii, and also from Sacramento, California to Kahului, Hawaii.[46]
On September 27, 2010 Alaska Airlines began service between Seattle and Lambert-St. Louis International Airport.[47][48]
